com.communote.plugins.api.rest.v30.resource

Class RestApiMultivaluedMapWrapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.communote.plugins.api.rest.v30.resource.RestApiMultivaluedMapWrapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<String,T>

    public class RestApiMultivaluedMapWrapper<T>
extends Object
implements Map<String,T>
    Wraps a MultivaluedMap so that by default the first entry will be returned at get. However the wrapper can be configured to join parameters by "," if the parameters name is defined in commaSeparatedParameters (as passed to the constructor). For example if the values "f_userIds" is set in the commaSeparatedParameters list then get() will join all values of the multivalued map. If the multivalued map contains two value "1,2" and "45" then the result will be "1,2,45"
    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/
